http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Two-boys-drown-in-Yagachi-Left-Bank-Canal/article14017641.ece

Two boys drowned in Yagachi Left Bank Canal at Chikkabedikere near Belur on Saturday evening.The deceased have been identified as Mohammed (13) and Naveed (12). Both are residents of Nehru Nagar in Belur town. They were students of Arabic school in Chikkamagaluru. After school hours, they had been to the canal around 4 p.m. They had not informed their parents about their visit to the canal.When the boys, who were unable to swim, cried for help, people nearby jumped into the water to rescue them. However, they could not save the boys. The bodies were recovered and shifted to Belur hospital for post-mortem. The Belur police have registered a case.